IMG2IMG CHAINING WORKFLOW — SD3.5 Large

This workflow generates 3 intermediate frames between each pair of your keyframes using SD3.5 img2img.

HOW TO USE:
1. Load your keyframes into the LoadImage nodes (green headers)
2. Edit prompts to describe the transition at each step
3. Denoise steps from 0.35 → 0.45 → 0.55 — adjust per pair
4. Run the workflow — outputs save to keyframes/transitions/
5. Combine all frames in order, then run RIFE for final smoothing

FRAME ORDER FOR FINAL VIDEO:
frame_001 → trans_01a → trans_01b → trans_01c → frame_002 → trans_02a → trans_02b → trans_02c → frame_003

TRANSITION 2: frame_002 → frame_003

Generate 3 intermediate frames. Prompts should blend
gradually between your mid and end keyframe descriptions.

TRANSITION 1: frame_001 → frame_002

Generate 3 intermediate frames. Prompts should blend
gradually between your start and mid keyframe descriptions.
